qas.question: What brand of cruise ships has a special importance to Southampton?
What was the name of the liner that left Southampton on its final journey on November 11, 2008?
Who christened the Cunard ship Queen Victoria in December 2007?
In what year did the Queen Elizabeth receive its name from the Queen?
What ship did the Duchess of Cambridge christen on June 13, 2013?

context: The city has a particular connection to <a0_0>Cunard Line<a0_0/> and their fleet of ships. This was particularly evident on 11 November 2008 when the Cunard liner <a1_0>RMS Queen Elizabeth 2<a1_0/> departed the city for the final time amid a spectacular fireworks display after a full day of celebrations. Cunard ships are regularly launched in the city, for example Queen Victoria was named by <a2_0>HRH The Duchess of Cornwall<a2_0/> in December 2007, and the Queen named Queen Elizabeth in the city during October <a3_0>2011<a3_0/>. The Duchess of Cambridge performed the naming ceremony of <a4_0>Royal Princess<a4_0/> on 13 June 2013.
